<subSubSection id="C331B6BF2A2544538ACFF8692E17FABA" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="176" pageId="18" pageNumber="175" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B94E5342A2544538ACFF8692D65FEBE" blockId="18.[151,1437,1929,2028]" lastBlockId="19.[151,1437,151,501]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="176" pageId="18" pageNumber="175">
<emphasis id="B95F39262A2544528ACFF8692E6DF848" bold="true" box="[199,315,2001,2027]" pageId="18" pageNumber="175">Remarks.</emphasis>
The description of this species is omitted because accurate descriptions are available in several papers, some very recent (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA98C52A2444538BFFFF2F2C67FF12" author="Reverter-Gil, O. &amp; Souto, J." box="[503,817,151,177]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" pagination="2735 - 2752" refId="ref14859" refString="Reverter-Gil, O. &amp; Souto, J. (2019) Watersiporidae (Bryozoa) in Iberian waters: an update on alien and native species. Marine Biodiversity, 49, 2735 - 2752. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12526 - 019 - 01003 - 4" type="journal article" year="2019">Reverter-Gil &amp; Souto 2019</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA98C52A2444538936FF2F2B7AFF12" author="Ramalho, L. V. &amp; Rodrigues-Aporta, R. &amp; Gofas, S." box="[830,1068,151,177]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" pagination="53 - 91" refId="ref14765" refString="Ramalho, L. V., Rodrigues-Aporta, R. &amp; Gofas, S. (2022) Preliminary account on the bryozoans of the Alboran platform (Western Mediterranean), with description of two new species. Zootaxa, 5094 (1), 53 - 91. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5094.1.2" type="journal article" year="2022">
Ramalho 
<emphasis id="B95F39262A24445389A4FF2F2CB0FF12" box="[940,998,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">et al.</emphasis>
2022
</bibRefCitation>
). However, the original material described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA98C52A2444538B3CFF032EB3FF75" author="Norman, A. M." box="[308,485,187,214]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" pagination="82 - 90" refId="ref14230" refString="Norman, A. M. (1864) On undescribed British Hydrozoa, Actinozoa and Polyzoa. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 13, 82 - 90. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222936408681578" type="journal article" year="1864">Norman (1864)</bibRefCitation>
has never been described and/or illustrated. The 
<typeStatus id="54905B962A2444538E2FFF032B28FF76" box="[1063,1150,187,213]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">syntype</typeStatus>
SMNH-Type-1772 (
<figureCitation id="1310F9B12A2444538F67FF032F9FFF5A" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1027,1051]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,525,1004]" captionTargetId="figure-163@19.[156,1431,525,1004]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 10. Terwasipora complanata (Norman, 1864), Holotype SMNH-Type-1772, Ireland. A. General view of the colony. B. Label on the underside of the rock substrate. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B = 3 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6424530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6424530/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
) consists of a fan-shaped colony, about 5.8 x 
<quantity id="4CD348D12A24445388CAFF672C4CFF5A" box="[706,794,223,249]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.6" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" unit="mm" value="8.6">8.6 mm</quantity>
, encrusting a granitic rock, about 9 x 
<quantity id="4CD348D12A2444538EB3FF662A41FF5A" box="[1211,1303,222,249]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" unit="cm" value="11.5">11.5 cm</quantity>
, sharing the substrate with spirorbid polychaetes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B94E5342A2444538ACFFE9F2E3CFE56" blockId="19.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA98C52A2444538ACFFE9F2E21FEE1" author="Norman, A. M." box="[199,375,295,322]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" pagination="82 - 90" refId="ref14230" refString="Norman, A. M. (1864) On undescribed British Hydrozoa, Actinozoa and Polyzoa. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 13, 82 - 90. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222936408681578" type="journal article" year="1864">Norman (1864)</bibRefCitation>
acknowledged having found the specimen in the collection of British Zoophytes of his late friend Mr. Barlee that he inherited. This information agrees with the label (
<figureCitation id="1310F9B12A24445389D5FEF32B14FEC6" box="[989,1090,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1027,1051]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,525,1004]" captionTargetId="figure-163@19.[156,1431,525,1004]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 10. Terwasipora complanata (Norman, 1864), Holotype SMNH-Type-1772, Ireland. A. General view of the colony. B. Label on the underside of the rock substrate. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B = 3 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6424530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6424530/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
), as does the description of the substrate provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA98C52A2444538B86FED72D6CFE29" author="Norman, A. M." box="[398,570,367,394]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" pagination="82 - 90" refId="ref14230" refString="Norman, A. M. (1864) On undescribed British Hydrozoa, Actinozoa and Polyzoa. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 13, 82 - 90. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222936408681578" type="journal article" year="1864">Norman (1864)</bibRefCitation>
as coarse-grained granite. While 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA98C52A24445389A7FED72B0AFE29" author="Norman, A. M." box="[943,1116,367,394]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" pagination="82 - 90" refId="ref14230" refString="Norman, A. M. (1864) On undescribed British Hydrozoa, Actinozoa and Polyzoa. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 13, 82 - 90. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222936408681578" type="journal article" year="1864">Norman (1864)</bibRefCitation>
claimed not to have detailed information about the collecting locality, apart from being British, the label reports 
<collectingCountry id="F33CA5A42A2444538E40FE2B2BC1FE0E" box="[1096,1175,403,429]" name="Ireland" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">Ireland</collectingCountry>
as the probable origin, which seems plausible given that the geology of the northern coast of 
<collectingCountry id="F33CA5A42A24445389ACFE0F2CA5FE72" box="[932,1011,439,465]" name="Ireland" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">Ireland</collectingCountry>
is characterized by igneous rocks and granitic intrusions.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF54B5BC2A2444538A9FFBBB2C9FFB9C" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6424530" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6424530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6424530/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" startId="19.[151,250,1027,1051]" targetBox="[156,1431,525,1004]" targetPageId="19">
<paragraph id="8B94E5342A2444538A9FFBBB2C9FFB9C" blockId="19.[151,1437,1027,1088]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis id="B95F39262A2444538A9FFBBB2E76FBB8" bold="true" box="[151,288,1027,1051]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">FIGURE 10.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2B9EB72A2444538B2FFBBC2D87FBBF" authority="(Norman, 1864)" baseAuthorityName="Norman" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[295,721,1028,1052]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Watersiporidae" genus="Terwasipora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="complanata">
<emphasis id="B95F39262A2444538B2FFBBC2D73FBBF" box="[295,549,1028,1052]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">Terwasipora complanata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA98C52A244453883BFBBC2D9DFBBF" author="Norman, A. M." box="[563,715,1028,1052]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176" pagination="82 - 90" refId="ref14230" refString="Norman, A. M. (1864) On undescribed British Hydrozoa, Actinozoa and Polyzoa. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 13, 82 - 90. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222936408681578" type="journal article" year="1864">Norman, 1864</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, Holotype SMNH-Type-1772, Ireland. A. General view of the colony. B. Label on the underside of the rock substrate. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B = 3 cm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B94E5342A2444538ACFFBD62E17FABA" blockId="19.[151,1436,1134,1305]" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">
This species has a wide Atlanto-Mediterranean distribution. Confirmed records are from the 
<collectingRegion id="49EF2BD62A2444538EDAFBD62A3DFB2B" box="[1234,1387,1134,1160]" country="United Kingdom" name="Isles of Scilly" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">Isles of Scilly</collectingRegion>
(off 
<collectingRegion id="49EF2BD62A2444538A9FFB2A2E54FB0F" box="[151,258,1170,1196]" country="United Kingdom" name="Cornwall" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">Cornwall</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33CA5A42A2444538B18FB2A2E39FB0E" box="[272,367,1170,1197]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="19" pageNumber="176">England</collectingCountry>
) encrusting shells and rocks (
